name: E. Three Strings
input: InputThe first line of the input contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^3$$$) — the number of test cases.The first line of each test case contains one string of lowercase Latin letters $$$a$$$ ($$$1 \leq |a| \leq 10^3$$$) — the first string, where $$$|a|$$$ denotes the length of string $$$a$$$.The second line of each test case contains one string of lowercase Latin letters $$$b$$$ ($$$1 \leq |b| \leq 10^3$$$) — the second string, where $$$|b|$$$ denotes the length of string $$$b$$$.The third line of each test case contains one string of lowercase Latin letters $$$c$$$ ($$$|c| = |a| + |b|$$$) — the third string.It is guaranteed that the sum of $$$|a|$$$ across all test cases does not exceed $$$2 \cdot 10^3$$$. Also, the sum of $$$|b|$$$ across all test cases does not exceed $$$2 \cdot 10^3$$$.
output: OutputFor each test case, output a single integer — the minimum number of characters that could have been changed in string $$$c$$$.
